  "text": "Studies [CITATION_1] ) assumed a scenario that the recharged energy is infinite and the sensor network stays operational forever. In this paper, we focus on a different situation where the total amount of energy assigned for the network is limited to E [CITATION_2] . Specifically, E equals to the sum of sensors' initial and recharged energy. (Since the total amount energy is limited and the time for each charge is confined to less than U max , we have limited the battery capacity to a suitable range.)",
